Diagnosis. Dorsum distinctly, finely punctate, not with micropunctation only (as in
O. mimikanus
). Clypeal apex rounded(-truncate), margin not reflexed. Eye foramina very large, distinctly open behind, i.e. , tapering posterior end of gena by far not reaching occipital side; interocular distance approximately 2.3 eye widths. Genal border rounded. Head and pronotum without any elevations. Generally brown(-black), dorsum shiny, not sericeous. Small, body length approximately 5 mm . Pygidium simply punctate. Females probably very similar, possibly with more rugulate-punctate clypeus, as in other species (see Variation and sexual dimorphism, below).
